We recommended that Management:

Require the Municipal Accountant and the Acting Municipal Treasurer to reconcile the specific items of their records on misclassified PPE items and the Municipal Accountant to draw a journal entry voucher to effect the necessary adjustments to correct the misclassified accounts;

Direct the Acting Municipal Treasurer to prepare the report on physical count of the PPE in accordance with Section 215 of GAM for LGUs to facilitate the reconciliation of the PPE with the Accounting records;

Require the Head, Inventory Committee to identify and locate all unserviceable properties for disposal in accordance with the procedures in the disposal of properties; and


Direct the Acting Municipal Treasurer to issue Property Acknowledgement Receipts of PPE transferred to the officials and employees of the Municipality.

We recommended that Management:

Inform the Acting Municipal Treasurer to periodically render Report on Local Road Networks; 

Require the Municipal Engineer to provide the Municipal Accountant and the Acting Municipal Treasurer with the complete description and cost segregation of road components for road projects; 


Instruct the Acting Municipal Treasurer to prepare and maintain the Local Road Network Property Card for all roads and its components as required in COA Circular No. 2015-008;

Instruct the Municipal Accountant to disclose the Road Network System in the Notes to the Financial Statement as required in COA Circular No. 2015-008 dated November 23, 2015; and

Direct the Municipal Accountant and Acting Municipal Treasurer, in coordination with the Municipal Engineer, to strictly adhere to the accounting and reporting guidelines on the Local Road Asset Management System.

